Pour the @water{700%ml} into a #pot and add the @chicken stock pot{1} and @star anise{1}. Bring to the boil on high heat. Stir well to dissolve the chicken stock pot and then add the @basmati rice{350%g}. Reduce the heat to medium, pop a #lid on and cook the rice for ~{10%minutes}. After 10 mins, remove the #pot from the heat. Leave to one side for another ~{10%minutes}, the rice will finish cooking in its own steam.

> Tip: The rice will stay hot in the pot while you cook everything else.

While your rice cooks, get on with the rest of your prep. Start by prepping and cooking the chicken. Slice each @British chicken breasts{4}(sliced widthways into pieces roughly ½cm thick).

Pop a large #frying pan{} or #wok on high heat and add a splash of @oil{}. Cook your chicken for ~{7-9%minutes}, stirring every now and again to make sure it browns and cooks evenly.

> Tip: Do this in batches if necessary to avoid overcrowding the pan. The chicken is cooked when the centre is no longer pink.

As the chicken cooks, prep your veggies. Cut the @red onion{1}(cut in half through the root) in half through the root. Peel and then slice into thin half moon shapes. Remove the core from the @purple pepper{1}(core removed) and @white pepper{1}(core removed) and slice into ½cm thick strips. Quarter the @Braeburn apple{1}, remove the pips and then chop each piece into 1cm chunks. Keep to one side.

Peel and grate the @garlic clove{1}(peeled and grated) (or use a #garlic press{} if you have one). Remove the roots from the @spring onion{3} and then slice as thinly as you can. Mix the @ketchup{6%tsp} with the @soy sauce{3%tsp} and keep to one side; this is your magic potion!

When your chicken is cooked, remove to a #plate and wipe out the #frying pan with #kitchen paper{}. Add a splash of @oil{} and your apple to the #frying pan. Stir fry your apple for ~{5-7%minutes} or until nicely brown and caramelised.

> Tip: The apple pieces should be soft. Remove from the pan.

Next, add your red onion and peppers to the same #pan and cook for ~{5%minutes}. Return your chicken and add the garlic to the #pan and cook for another ~{3%minutes} until your chicken is piping hot.

Add your magic potion and stir well to make sure everything is well coated.

Remove the star anise from the rice and fluff it up with a #fork. Mix through your spring onion. Serve a generous amount of rice on each #plate, top with your spooky stir-fry and then finish with your caramelised apple. Enjoy!!